				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I know for sure that you'll have to make sure the &quot;expansion connector&quot; isn't accessed during reads; it'll cause bus conflicts between the two cartridges as you mentioned. Something like {PRG /CE} OR {PRG R/W} going to the expansion {PRG /CE} should do this trick for all mappers except MMC5 and N163, which would need also !{PRG R/W} AND {PRG A14} going to expansion {PRG A14}. And then, it would be mostly fine. I'm afraid diodes on D* lines won't do the trick, though: it will interfere with reads, no matter how you place your diodes.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

